<!-- RESEARCH -->
<section id="research">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Research &amp; Context</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">What Already Exists — and Why It's Not Enough</h2>
  <div class="blue-bar"></div>
  <div class="research-layout">
    <div class="research-text">
      <p>EruvGuard did not emerge in a vacuum. Before developing our system, we researched existing eruv monitoring technology and studied established eruv organizations to understand the current landscape of available solutions.</p>
      <p>Some large-scale eruvin — most notably the <strong>Manhattan Eruv</strong> — have implemented forms of automated monitoring to assist with maintenance. These systems confirm that automated eruv supervision is both technically possible and halachically validated. The Manhattan Eruv's infrastructure serves as an important proof-of-concept, and we acknowledge their pioneering work.</p>
      <p>However, existing automated systems carry significant limitations. Their high cost — estimated at approximately <strong>$200,000 per year</strong> — places them out of reach for the vast majority of communities. They are also custom-built for a single, specific eruv and cannot be redeployed without substantial reinvestment.</p>
      <p>EruvGuard is designed to close this gap: an affordable, modular, and community-agnostic solution that any eruv can adopt without prohibitive financial investment.</p>
      <div class="source-credit">
        <strong>Acknowledged Source</strong>
        Manhattan Eruv Organization — automated monitoring technology and infrastructure. Cited as a foundational precedent for large-scale eruv supervision systems.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="compare-card">
      <h4>EruvGuard vs. Existing Systems</h4>
      <div class="cmp-row">
        <span class="cmp-lbl">Annual Cost</span>
        <span class="cmp-them">~$200,000</span>
        <span class="cmp-us">Fraction of that</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-row">
        <span class="cmp-lbl">Portability</span>
        <span class="cmp-them">Fixed / custom</span>
        <span class="cmp-us">Universally adaptable</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-row">
        <span class="cmp-lbl">Scalability</span>
        <span class="cmp-them">Single eruv only</span>
        <span class="cmp-us">Any size eruv</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-row">
        <span class="cmp-lbl">Maintenance</span>
        <span class="cmp-them">Requires specialists</span>
        <span class="cmp-us">Low-maintenance</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-row">
        <span class="cmp-lbl">Community Reach</span>
        <span class="cmp-them">Major metros only</span>
        <span class="cmp-us">Any community</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-row">
        <span class="cmp-lbl">Power Source</span>
        <span class="cmp-them">Grid-dependent</span>
        <span class="cmp-us">Solar + battery</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

