<!-- AUDIENCE -->
<section id="audience">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Who It's For</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Target Audience &amp; Limitations</h2>
  <div class="blue-bar"></div>
  <div class="audience-split">
    <div>
      <p class="section-subtitle" style="margin-bottom:4px;">EruvGuard is built for any Jewish community with an eruv — large or small, urban or suburban. The size of your eruv does not matter.</p>
      <ul class="audience-list">
        <li>
          <div class="aud-icon">🕍</div>
          <div class="aud-text">
            <strong>Rabbis &amp; Religious Authorities</strong>
            <span>Receive instant, halachically relevant alerts and manage eruv validity with confidence — no more end-of-week uncertainty.</span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="aud-icon">👥</div>
          <div class="aud-text">
            <strong>Eruv Inspectors &amp; Volunteers</strong>
            <span>Replace exhausting weekly perimeter walks with targeted, alert-driven maintenance — saving hundreds of hours each year.</span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="aud-icon">🏘️</div>
          <div class="aud-text">
            <strong>The Wider Jewish Community</strong>
            <span>Any community member who relies on a valid eruv for Shabbat benefits from a more dependable, consistently maintained boundary.</span>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="limits-box">
      <h4>Known Limitations</h4>
      <div class="lim-item">
        <div class="lim-dot"></div>
        <p><strong>Weight:</strong> If the device is too heavy, it could strain or snap thin eruv strings. The team is minimizing weight through design iteration and lighter materials.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lim-item">
        <div class="lim-dot"></div>
        <p><strong>Size:</strong> A device that is too large or bulky could interfere with the eruv line. Future versions aim to significantly reduce form factor.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lim-item">
        <div class="lim-dot"></div>
        <p><strong>Weather resistance:</strong> Current housing uses PLA filament, which is less weather-resistant. A planned upgrade to ALA filament will improve outdoor durability.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lim-item">
        <div class="lim-dot"></div>
        <p><strong>Pressure sensing:</strong> Current version detects positional changes. A planned load cell will enable direct tension sensing for even greater accuracy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

